        <briefdescription>
<para>This function performs SHA2 Known Answer Tests (KAT&apos;s). </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ClientParamPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the XAsu_ClientParams structure which holds the client input parameters. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Sha2Mode</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>SHA2 mode to test KAT (XASU_SHA_MODE_256 or XASU_SHA_MODE_512).</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if IPI request to ASU is sent successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_ARGUMENT, if any argument is invalid.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_QUEUE_FULL, if Queue buffer is full.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if sending an IPI request to ASU fails.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID, if received Queue ID is invalid. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate input parameters.</para><para>Generate unique ID and register the callback.</para><para>Create command header.</para><para>Update request buffer and send an IPI request to ASU. </para>        </inbodydescription>
